================================================================================
Dwarf Fortress artwork -- what this repository does and does not contain
================================================================================

    The Dwarf Fortress graphics are the copyrighted artwork of Bay 12 Games /
    Kitfox Games and are NOT redistributed in this repository, with one
    documented exception (the curses interface font, next section).

    The web client's composite sprites (dwarf.png, dwarf_dark.png,
    dwarf_female.png, animal_people_flat.png, item_chair_composite.png,
    item_hatch_composite.png, item_table_composite.png, favicon.png) are
    derived from the paid DF graphics, so their PIXELS are never shipped.
    Instead the repository ships host/sprite_recipe.json -- crop, blit, and
    palette-remap COORDINATES only, generated by tools/ws2/emit_sprite_recipe.py
    -- and host/bake_sprites.mjs composites the actual images at install time
    from the HOST'S OWN Dwarf Fortress install (which is also where all other
    game art is served from at runtime). Copies of these composites were
    removed from this repository and its published history on 2026-07-14, and
    tools/harness/sprite_provenance_gate_test.mjs fails the test suite if any
    derived sprite is ever committed again.

================================================================================
Third-party artwork  --  web/fonts/df-curses.ttf
================================================================================

    web/fonts/df-curses.ttf is a TrueType font generated by
    tools/ws2/build_df_font.mjs from the Dwarf Fortress interface tileset
    (data/art/curses_640x300.png -- the 8x12 CP437 bitmap font named by
    [FONT:] in DF's data/init/init_default.txt).

    The GLYPH SHAPES are the artwork of Bay 12 Games and are NOT covered by
    this project's AGPL-3.0-only license. They are included so the web client
    can reproduce Dwarf Fortress's own interface typography. All rights in the
    Dwarf Fortress artwork remain with Bay 12 Games / Kitfox Games. This font
    is the ONLY Bay 12 artwork contained in the repository (see the previous
    section for how everything else is produced on the host's machine).

    The conversion tool (tools/ws2/build_df_font.mjs) is our own work and is
    AGPL-3.0-only like the rest of this project. It is committed and
    re-runnable, so the font can be regenerated from any DF install:

        node tools/ws2/build_df_font.mjs --atlas "<DF>/data/art/curses_640x300.png"

    If redistribution of the derived font is ever contested, DELETE
    web/fonts/df-curses.ttf and serve the atlas at runtime instead: the plugin
    already mounts the DF install's data/art at /dfart (src/http_server.cpp),
    which makes the glyph source reachable from the browser without shipping
    any Bay 12 artwork in this repository.
